General Information

Type of Jurisdiction: Archdiocese

Elevated: 9 August 1952

Metropolitan See

Rite: Latin (or Roman)

State: Kansas

Country: United States of America

Square Kilometers: 32,437 (12,528 Square Miles)

Description: The Archdiocese is comprised of the following 21 counties of the State of Kansas: Anderson, Atchison, Brown, Coffey, Doniphan, Douglas, Franklin, Jackson, Jefferson, Johnson, Leavenworth, Linn, Lyon, Marshall, Miami, Nemaha, Osage, Pottawatomie, Shawnee, Wabaunsee and Wyandotte.

Conference Region: IX (IA, KS, MO, NE)

Catholic Directory Abbreviation: KCK

Official Web Site: http://www.archkck.org/

Archdiocesan Newspaper: http://www.theleaven.com/

Mailing Address: 12615 Parallel Parkway, Kansas City, KS 66109, USA

Telephone: (913)721-1570

Fax: 721-1577
